\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 14. G. viridiflorum} Boiss. & Reuter,{\i  Pugillus} 51 (1852). Stem 40-80 cm, fairly stout. Leaves 13-30 × 4-6(-8) mm, broadly lanceolate to oblanceolate, mostly abruptly narrowed to the awned apex, rough above, with rather dense, patent long hairs beneath. Inflorescence long, cylindrical; partial inflorescences dense; pedicels 1-3 mm, slender. Corolla 2·5-3 mm in diameter, rotate, greenish-yellow; lobes 1-1·5 mm, more or less triangular, acute to apiculate. Filaments 0·4-0·5 mm; anthers 0·2-0·3 mm, subglobose to ovoid. Fruit 1-1·5 mm, granulate and with long, dense, patent hairs.{\i  Shady river-banks. • S.W. Spain} ({\i near Ronda}). Hs.
