\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 16. G. palustre} L., {\i Sp. Pl. }105 (1753). Stems (5-)15-70(-80) cm, slender, procumbent to erect, smooth or usually more or less retrorsely aculeolate on the scarcely whitish angles. Middle cauline leaves 5-20 × 1-3 mm, in whorls of 4-6, narrowly to broadly oblanceolate, obtuse, more or less patent; margin more or less flat, often rough. Inflorescence many-flowered, cylindrical; partial inflorescences rather dense; pedicels 1-4 mm, slightly elongating after anthesis, divaricate in fruit. Flowers (3)4-merous; corolla (1·5-)2-3(-3·5) mm in diameter. Fruit 2-3 mm, more or less smooth. 2n = 24, 48. {\i Wet places. Almost throughout Europe}. All except ?Al Az ?Bl Cr ?Rs (K) Sb ?Tu.
