\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 19. G. saturejifolium} Trev.,{\i  Ges. Naturf Freunde Berlin Mag.}{\b  7}: 146 (1815). Stems (30-)50-70(-80) cm, slender, erect; lateral non-flowering shoots, particularly in the middle, subterete and rather smooth below, with 4 whitish angles and rough with patent papillae above. Leaves (18-)25-28(-35) × (2-)3(-4) mm, in whorls of 4-6, linear-lanceolate, blackish when dried, dull with short cartilaginous apex and rather smooth mid-vein, with antrorsely directed papilliform teeth on the revolute margin and upper surface. Inflorescence many-flowered, ovoid; branches bracteate, papillose, divaricate after anthesis. Pedicels 1-2(-3) mm. Corolla (1·8-)2(-2·2) mm in diameter, white, rotate; lobes shortly apiculate. Fruit 1-1·5 mm, ovoid, papillose.{\i  Marshes. Volga delta.} Rs (E).
